6 point graph Is there disproportionate education attainment by race in the county?

According to the graph, the answer is yes. Among the bay area population of 25 years or older, there are noticeable differences in the educational attainment across races. There are proportionally less white people having education attainment that is either less than high school diploma or high school diploma equivalent. White people have proportionally more people getting some college/associates degree or bachelor degree/higher. Black or African Americans have proportionally more people getting some college degree but less getting bachelor degree or higher. Asians have proportionally less people getting high school diploma equivalent but more getting bachelors degree or higher. Some other race alone category have proportionally more people getting education that is either less than high school diploma or high school diploma equivalent. There are proportionally less of them getting bachelors degree or higher. Other races in general shares only small percentage of the population and can be harder to read from the graph.
